'''活躍用戶'''（{{lang-en|Active users}}）數是衡量[[互聯網|互聯網]]產品（例如[[社交網絡服務|社交網絡服務]]、[[在線遊戲|在線遊戲]]或[[移動應用|移動應用]]）成功與否的性能指標，它衡量在給定的時間間隔內有多少用戶訪問該產品或服務或與該產品或服務進行交互。<ref name=":0">Henry, Theresa F., et al. [http://link.galegroup.com/apps/doc/A381838689/ITBC?u=clackamasccl&sid=ITBC&xid=81e00621 "Socially awkward: social media companies' nonfinancial metrics can send a mixed message."] ''Journal of Accountancy'', Sept. 2014, p. 52+. ''Business Collection''. Accessed October 25, 2018.</ref>通常以'''[[月活躍用戶數|每月活躍用戶]]'''（'''MAU'''）<ref>{{cite web  | title = AppStore knowledge base by AppStoreGrowth : MAU  | url = https://www.appstoregrowth.com/knowledge-base/mau/  | access-date = 2020-08-07  | archive-date = 2021-03-08  | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308140213/https://www.appstoregrowth.com/knowledge-base/mau/  | dead-url = no  }}</ref>、'''每週活躍用戶'''（'''WAU'''）<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-02-16|title=How Slack Plans to Make It Easier to Chat With Colleagues at Other Companies|url=http://fortune.com/2017/09/12/slack-shared-channels/|website=Fortune|first=Barb|last=Darrow|date=2017-09-12|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224125123/https://fortune.com/2017/09/12/slack-shared-channels/|dead-url=no}}</ref>、'''每天活躍用戶'''（'''DAU'''）<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-02-16|title=Twitter reveals its daily active user numbers for the first time|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/02/07/twitter-reveals-its-daily-active-user-numbers-first-time/|website=The Washington Post|first=Hamza|last=Shaban|date=2019-02-07|archive-date=2021-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417172800/https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/02/07/twitter-reveals-its-daily-active-user-numbers-first-time/|dead-url=no}}</ref>或'''peak concurrent users'''（'''PCU'''）來評估該指標）。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.lawinsider.com/dictionary/peak-concurrent-users |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-08-07 |archive-date=2020-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408034208/https://www.lawinsider.com/dictionary/peak-concurrent-users |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

==使用==
任何時間尺度上的活躍用戶都可以大致了解產品保持的回頭客數量，並且可以通過比較此數量上的變化來預測消費者數量的增長或下降。

DAU與MAU的比率提供了一種基本的方法來估算一段時間內的[[客戶參與度|客戶參與度]]和保留率。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Hui|first=Sam|date=2017-02-27|title=Understanding repeat playing behavior in casual games using a Bayesian data augmentation approach|url=https://rady.ucsd.edu/docs/seminars/hui.pdf|journal=Quantitative Marketing and Economics|volume=15|pages=29–55|via=Springer Link|doi=10.1007/s11129-017-9180-2|access-date=2020-08-07|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308065709/https://rady.ucsd.edu/docs/seminars/hui.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>較高的比率表示較大的保留概率，這通常表示產品成功。比率0.15和更高被認為是增長的轉折點，而持續比率0.2或更高則標誌著持久的成功。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamesbrief.com/2011/10/daumau-engagement/|title=DAU/MAU = engagement|last=Lovell|first=Nicholas|date=2011-10-26|website=Gamesbrief|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308140435/https://www.gamesbrief.com/2011/10/daumau-engagement/|archive-date=2021-03-08|access-date=2019-12-03}}</ref>

活躍的用戶數據可用於確定高流量時段，並創建用於[[定向廣告|定向廣告]]的用戶行為模型。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Li|first=Lin|last2=Li|first2=Ang|last3=Hao|first3=Bibo|last4=Guan|first4=Zengda|last5=Zhu|first5=Tingshao|date=2014-01-23|title=Predicting Active Users' Personality Based on Micro-Blogging Behaviors|url=http://europepmc.org/backend/ptpmcrender.fcgi?accid=PMC3898945&blobtype=pdf|journal=PLOS ONE|volume=9|issue=1|pages=e84997|via=Open Access|pmid=24465462|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0084997|pmc=3898945|bibcode=2014PLoSO...984997L|access-date=2020-08-07|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224095338/http://europepmc.org/backend/ptpmcrender.fcgi?accid=PMC3898945&blobtype=pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
